title: Grateful Dead Live at Saenger Performing Arts Center on 1980-10-19
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi 1000-II > Sound Devices USB Pre-2 > WAV 2496. Edits: WAV 2496 > Wavelab > CD-Wave (24bit output) > TLH > FLAC 2496 tagged. Concert recording & transfer by Richie Stankiewicz, edits by Andrew F. 09/2013.
description:
Set 1

On The Road Again, Jack A Roe, Dark Hollow, Rosalie McFall, Cassidy, Bird Song, Heaven Help The Fool, Ain't No Lie-> Ripple

Set 2

Jack Straw, They Love Each Other, Mama Tried, Mexicali Blues, Candyman, Passenger, Row Jimmy-> Looks Like Rain-> Tennessee Jed-> Promised Land

Set 3

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Samson & Delilah, Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia-> Good Lovin', E: Brokedown Palace

First Set Acoustic

reviews.review_text:
Sound quality Wow.

Beyer Mics were the perfect match for this room.  

***** for sound quality in electric sets alone.
grate pull in N O really nice sound.thank you for taping!!!!!
- Wonderful. I've been listening to the Dead on the Archive for about three years, and I'm pretty sure this is the best sounding show I've ever heard, both in terms of sound and playing.
Love it Love it love love it.  Great theater good sound.

Great Recording!! Thanks Rich you were always their in the 80's every show I went to.

Ed ;)

Another Classic Richie S. Another classic pull from one of the best ever to hoist a pair of mics. Crystal clear. Beyer M160s (ribbon hypercard) a fantastic microphone in the hands of someone who know what he is doing. 20 foot spread. Also, a GREAT show.
